<br>
Do you need to be able to solo easily?<br>
Do you want to play a melee class or caster?<br>
If melee, do you want to play a caster melee, or pure melee?<br>
If caster...<br>
Which kinds of spells do you want to be able to cast a lot? a little?<br>
-pets<br>
-heals<br>
-buffs<br>
-debuffs<br>
-crowd control related<br>
-DDs<br>
-dots<br>
<br>
Equipment in this day is pretty cheap for really good stuff.  You can buy some excellent gear for just about any class without much PP if you know what you are looking for, and where to find it.  Some classes are much easier to equip for cheaper than others.  For example, with about 4k PP, you could equip a monk with gear that will last him into his 50s.  If you can find some people hunting in thurg, you can get some fine platemail armor that usually just rots.  Pet classes can slack on getting decent gear as they can use their pets in lieu of hp and ac gear.<br>
<br>
Another thing too, is that for some classes, lots of spells are junk, or of minimal use.  For example, if I were to recreate a shaman, I doubt I'd even buy any stat spells until my 20s or 30s.  The low level ones just don't do much. <p>=============================
